    "Finally, building on the seminal calls of XAI researchers (Rudin, 2018; Arrieta et al., 2020), we believe in self-explaining methods as a promising path toward the \"holy grail\" of NLP: achieving intrinsic interpretability while minimizing performance degradation.",
    "Yet, as Table 3 indicates, only about 7% of papers focus on self-explaining models, leaving them largely underexplored.",
    "The LLM era presents new research opportunities.",
    "Despite the expectation that non-developers would benefit from concept-level, self-explaining, and causal-based methods, their adoption remains limited.",
    "We believe this is mainly due to the lack of research and development within the NLP community."
